## 01 — HERO SECTION

> The first thing every visitor sees — must work in under 5 seconds

The hero section is the most critical part of the entire page. It must immediately answer the question: "Who is this and why should I care?" — without the visitor having to scroll. Everything else on the page depends on the hero doing its job well.

### What Goes In

- **Lady Adel's professional photograph** — high quality, confident, warm expression, professional attire. Full upper body or portrait style. This is non-negotiable.
- **Her name** — large, prominent typography. "Lady Adel" should be unmissable.
- **Power statement** — a single line that captures everything she is, e.g.:

> *"Banker. Preacher. Business Coach. Empowering Faith-Driven Leaders Across Africa."*

- **Two CTA buttons side by side:**
  - `JOIN THE NEXT CATCH UP` → links to registration page
  - `WORK WITH ME` → scrolls down to the services section
- **Brand tagline** — "Faith. Business. Impact." displayed in IWC Concepts gold
- **Subtle brand elements** — IWC Concepts logo, brand colours (Purple, Gold, Navy)

### Writing Tone for This Section

Bold. Confident. Inviting. Lady Adel should feel like a leader who has earned her seat — not someone seeking validation. The hero speaks first to entrepreneurs and business leaders, then to everyone else.

