## 07 — THE ENTREPRENEUR PROGRAMME

> The paid flagship offering — detailed enough to make someone apply

This section is for the paid training programme currently being developed — the cohort-based growth programme for startups and scaling businesses. It needs enough detail that a serious entrepreneur can decide to apply, but enough mystery that they must contact you to know the full price.

### Programme Name Options

- **The IWC Growth Lab** — practical, enterprise-focused
- **The Lady Adel Business Accelerator** — uses her authority
- **The Faith & Business Bootcamp** — speaks to the spiritual angle
- **The Purposeful Entrepreneur Programme** — speaks to mission-driven founders
- **Build & Scale** — clean, direct, action-oriented

### Who It Is For

Be specific. A well-defined audience makes the right people say "this is exactly for me."

- Entrepreneurs with a business idea they are ready to build
- Startups in the first 1–3 years looking to get their fundamentals right
- Small business owners who have hit a growth ceiling and need a breakthrough
- Faith-driven professionals who want to align their business with their purpose
- Professionals transitioning into entrepreneurship

### What Participants Will Get

- **Training sessions and structured curriculum** — covering finance, brand, sales, leadership, systems, scaling
- **Business frameworks and templates** — practical tools they can use immediately in their business
- **Mentorship** — access to experienced entrepreneurs and industry experts
- **Strategic contacts** — curated introductions to relevant networks, investors and partners
- **Peer community** — a cohort of like-minded entrepreneurs for accountability and collaboration
- **Accountability structure** — regular check-ins, goal tracking and progress reviews
- **Certificate of completion** — recognised participation certificate from IWC Concepts

### Suggested Programme Structure

- Cohort-based: 10–30 participants per cohort
- Duration: 8–12 weeks (one session per week)
- Format: Live online sessions via Zoom (1.5–2 hours per session)
- Supplemented by: recorded resources, PDF frameworks and a private WhatsApp group
- Culminates in: a pitch session or business review presentation

### Investment (Pricing Strategy)

Do not publish the exact price on the webpage. Instead use "Fees available on application" or offer a tiered structure disclosed after enquiry. This filters serious applicants and allows Lady Adel to adjust pricing based on each cohort.

### Call to Action

- **Primary:** `APPLY NOW` button linking to the application form
- **Secondary:** `JOIN THE WAITLIST` for people not ready to apply yet

### FAQ Section

**Q: Who is this programme for?**
Entrepreneurs, startups, growing businesses and faith-driven professionals who want to build with purpose and strategy.

**Q: How many people are in each cohort?**
