## 11 — KEY DESIGN PRINCIPLES

> How the page should look, feel and perform

| Principle | Detail |
|-----------|--------|
| **Mobile-First** | Most of Lady Adel's audience will visit from smartphones. The page must look and function perfectly on mobile before anything else. |
| **Fast Loading** | Keep images compressed and optimised. Slow pages lose visitors. Aim for under 3 seconds load time on mobile data. |
| **One CTA Per Section** | Every section has one primary call to action. Do not overwhelm visitors with multiple choices — it leads to no choice. |
| **Brand Consistency** | Navy, Orange and Gold from the event flyer. Purple and Gold from IWC Concepts. These should appear consistently throughout. |
| **Floating WhatsApp** | A sticky WhatsApp icon at the bottom right of every page. Essential for Ghana market. Links to a pre-filled message. |
| **Google Analytics** | Install from day one. Track which sections people scroll to, how long they stay, and which CTAs they click. |
| **Accessibility** | Ensure sufficient colour contrast. All images must have alt text. Forms must be keyboard-navigable. |
| **Regular Updates** | The page must be updated after every Catch Up episode — new dates, speaker names, testimonials and episode links. |

